						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the central shrine in the Kailāsanātha temple.</p>						

						<p>Rājēndra III. Year 12: 1257-58 A.D.</p>						

						<p>In this inscription in verse the king is described as one who has captured the crown and city of the Pāṇḍya king and as <hi rend="italic">Vīrarākshasa and Rājākkaḷ-tambirāṉ.</hi><note n="288-2">cf., <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.</hi> Vol. IV. No. 511.</note></p>						

						<p>It seems to record a grant of land to god Śiva by Mallīśaṉ, probably a chief of Ambāḷūr.</p>						

						</summary>
